  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a Sub-Inspector (SI) in Delhi Police after graduation, follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Must be a graduate from a recognized university\n- Age limit: 20-25 years (relaxation for reserved categories)\n- Minimum height: 165 cm for males, 155 cm for females\n- Minimum chest measurement: 81 cm (for male candidates)\n\n2. Selection Process:\n- Written Exam (Preliminary and Main)\n- Physical Efficiency Test (PET)\n- Medical Examination\n- Personal Interview\n\n3. Recruitment Methods:\n- Direct Recruitment through Delhi Police Recruitment\n- Delhi Police SI Recruitment Notification\n- Through Staff Selection Commission (SSC)\n\n4. Required Documents:\n- Educational certificates\n- Age proof\n- Identity proof\n- Caste certificate (if applicable)\n\n5. Preparation Tips:\n- Study current affairs\n- Practice general knowledge\n- Solve previous years' question papers\n- Physical fitness training\n- Mock tests for written exams\n\n6. Important Websites:\n- Delhi Police Official Website\n- SSC Official Website\n\nRegularly check official notifications for exact details and application process.",
